The average translational diffusion rate can be measured by pulsed-field-gradient (PFG) NMR [25], often referred to as diffusion ordered spectroscopy (DOSY) [21, 22]. In this experiment, the diffusion coefficients can be estimated by varying the gradient amplitude (g) and fitting the experimental data to the theoretical Stejskal–Tanner Eq. 10 [26].
