\begin{document}$$\left( {\tau _ \bot  } \right)$$\end{document}; the ratio of the two correlation times can be used as a measure of anisotropy. Other parameters in the model-free approach are the internal correlation time (τe), the generalized order parameter (S2) and, in the anisotropic model, an angle (α).

